This page defines the '''income category vocabulary''' as an
indented bullet list. The ReceiptScanner extension parses it on save,
flattens it into full paths (<code>Sales/Products</code>,
<code>Consulting/Retainers</code>, …), and uses it to autocomplete the
<code>income_category</code> field on [[Form:Income]].

Expenses have their own vocabulary at [[Project:Expense categories]].

Edit this list with normal wiki editing to change the taxonomy. Existing
income entries keep whatever path they were saved with; see
[[Help:Receipts]] for how drift is handled.

'''Reserved characters in labels:''' <code>/</code> separates parent
from child in the rendered path, and <code>;</code> separates the
options when this list is fed to the form combobox. Don't use either
inside a label. Commas are fine. Where you'd be tempted to write
<code>A/B</code> in a single label, write "A, B, and …" instead, or
split into a real parent → child relationship.

This starter tree is a sensible default for a small business. Replace it
with your own.

* Sales
** Products
** Services
* Consulting
** Hourly
** Retainers
** Contracts
* Subscriptions
* Sponsorships
* Royalties
* Interest
* Dividends
* Rental Income
* Grants
* Refunds and Rebates
* Sale of Assets
* Other
